comment: A canonical version of ~ infxpen , by a completely different approach (although it uses ~ infxpen via ~ xpomen ). Using Cantor's normal form, we can show that ` A ^o B ` respects equinumerosity ( ~ oef1o ), so that all the steps of ` ( _om ^ W ) x. ( _om ^ W ) ~~ _om ^ ( 2 W ) ~~ ` ` ( _om ^ 2 ) ^ W ~~ _om ^ W ` can be verified using bijections to do the ordinal commutations. (The assumption on ` N ` can be satisfied using ~ cnfcom3c .) (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 30-May-2015.) (Revised by AV, 7-Jul-2019.)
